-- Istithmar in Mandarin Oriental Refinance Talks, Al-Khaleej Says
-- B y   Z a i n a b   F a t t a h
-- 2012-02-28T05:21:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-28/istithmar-in-mandarin-oriental-refinance-talks-al-khaleej-says.html
Dubai’s Istithmar PJSC is in talks
with a Chinese lender to refinance its $175 million mortgage on
the Mandarin Oriental New York Hotel in  Manhattan ’s Time Warner
Center,  Al-Khaleej newspaper  reported, citing unidentified
people within Istithmar.  The newspaper did not name the Chinese lender. The
investment firm, owned by Dubai’s government, bought the 248-
room hotel for $340 million in 2006.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zainab Fattah in Dubai at 
 zfattah@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net  